TLINE.TDLINE: &PURPOSE&
Creating Background Jobs for Billing
&INTEGRATION&
This program has been copied from standard program RV60SBAT(VF06).
&PREREQUISITES&
&FEATURES&
Program creates the child jobs based on the number of documents count
maintained in constant Table(DevID - E227)
If any one of the child jobs get cancelled, Status of the
main job would be cancelled.
Main job status is in Active until all child jobs got
finished.
If any child job gets cancelled, cancelled job would be
rescheduled once again, job name extending with "Res".
Detailed process information at runtime can be checked in main
job log.
Program leverages application servers only which are pertaining
to the server group entered on selection screen.
&SELECTION&
Server group is a mandatory field on selection screen.
Sales org. is a mandatory field on selection screen.
Number of jobs per servers is a mandatory field and defaulted on
selection screen.
Sales orders check box defaulted on selection screen.
Send immediately check box has been defaulted on selection screen.
Rest of the selection is same as VF06 program.
&STANDARD_VARIANTS&
&OUTPUT&
Main job spool will be displayed, it contains number of records which
means number of child jobs processed<(>,<)>
number of customers and number of documents processed in the job.
Child jobs spool contains actual billing documents output data.
&ACTIVITIES&
Program fetches documents based on input selection.
It opens the jobs based on the documents count maintained in constant
table.
Submits the step of program SDBILLDL(VF04) program.
Checks server's availability of input server group and compares the
availability percentage
-which is maintained in constant table DevID - E227.
Closes the job with available server.
Keeps posting job's log of each step.
&EXAMPLE&
VF06
